sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client (predicts)
    participant L as Link (lossy/laggy)
    participant S as Server (authoritative)
    C->>C: apply input instantly (predicted, lag-free)
    C->>L: send input seq N
    L-->>S: deliver after up-latency
    S->>S: apply, advance authoritative state
    S->>L: snapshot (state + ack=N)
    L-->>C: deliver after down-latency (may drop)
    C->>C: set confirmed, replay un-acked inputs
    Note over C,S: under latency the client leads, both converge
